{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584382","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584382"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:44:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:44:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14456"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14456","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14456"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.06,0.33,0.41,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7151"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113929"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7151","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7151"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14456"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"95944"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"40"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4903"},{"type":"tags","id":"4905"},{"type":"tags","id":"4914"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17076"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17135"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113929","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/113929"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a component of the adventitia of blood vessels?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Internal elastic membrane","Vasa vasorum interna","External elastic membrane","Vasa vasorum externa","Smooth muscle cells"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe adventitia, or tunica adventitia, is the outermost layer of a blood vessel and contains \u003Cstrong\u003Evasa vasorum externa\u003C/strong\u003E, which are small blood vessels that supply blood to the outer layers of the vessel wall. Understanding the components of blood vessel layers is crucial for comprehending vascular physiology and pathology.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einternal elastic membrane\u003C/strong\u003E is located between the tunica intima and tunica media, not in the adventitia. \u003Cstrong\u003EVasa vasorum interna\u003C/strong\u003E are found in the inner layers of large blood vessels, not in the adventitia. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eexternal elastic membrane\u003C/strong\u003E is located between the tunica media and tunica adventitia, not within the adventitia itself. \u003Cstrong\u003ESmooth muscle cells\u003C/strong\u003E are primarily found in the tunica media, not in the adventitia.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The adventitia of blood vessels contains vasa vasorum externa, which supply blood to the outer layers of the vessel wall.","The adventitia is the outermost layer of a blood vessel, composed of connective tissue and providing structural support."],"references":["Stenmark KR, Yeager ME, El Kasmi KC, Nozik-Grayck E, Gerasimovskaya EV, Li M, Riddle SR, Frid MG. The adventitia: essential regulator of vascular wall structure and function. Annu Rev Physiol. 2013;75:23-47. doi: 10.1146/annurev-physiol-030212-183802. Epub 2012 Dec 3. PMID: 23216413; PMCID: PMC3762248.","Majesky MW, Dong XR, Hoglund V, Mahoney WM Jr, Daum G. The adventitia: a dynamic interface containing resident progenitor cells. Arterioscler Thromb Vasc Biol. 2011 Jul;31(7):1530-9. doi: 10.1161/ATVBAHA.110.221549. PMID: 21677296; PMCID: PMC3382115.","Hemmings, H. C., \u0026 Egan, T. D. Pharmacology and physiology for anesthesia e-book: foundations and clinical application. 2012. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relations